title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Definition 9.1.3</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be a vector space over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> (usually a subfield of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, but if we can give <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> a sensible "absolute value" operation, then that works fine). A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Norm</html:dfn> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\left  \lVert  - \right  \rVert \colon  V\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> such that
<fr:ol><fr:li>Positive definiteness: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\left  \lVert  v \right  \rVert =0]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v=\vec {0}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Positive homogeneity: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\left  \lVert  av \right  \rVert =|a|\left  \lVert  v \right  \rVert ]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v\in  V]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Triangle inequality: <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\left  \lVert  v+w \right  \rVert \leq \left  \lVert  v \right  \rVert +\left  \lVert  w \right  \rVert ]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v,w\in  V]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p><fr:p>Observe these properties imply <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\left  \lVert  v \right  \rVert \geq 0]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[v\in  V]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
