display="inline"><![CDATA[d\colon  X\times  X\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> such that:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,x)=0]]></fr:tex>;</fr:li>
<fr:li>Positivity: For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  X]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y)\geq 0]]></fr:tex> and moreover <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y)=0]]></fr:tex> iff <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x=y]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>Symmetry: For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y\in  X]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y)=d(y,x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
<fr:li>Triangle inequality: For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y,z\in  X]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y)+d(y,z)\geq  d(x,z)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
